Exploration of mitigation date, relative contact rate and infectious days

library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(lubridate)
library(readr)
library(tidyr)
library(stringr)
library(forcats)

Introduction

I wanted to see how sensitive the CHIME projections are to values of the key input variables. Using my sim_chime_scenario_runner tool, I ran 560 scenarios based on the following ranges for each input factor:

  • mitigation-date : 2020-03-21 through 2020-03-27
  • relative-contact-rate : 0.05 to 0.80 in 0.05 increments
  • infectious-days : 8, 9, 10, 11 and 12 days

Here is the config file with values for all of the other inputs:

--population 5026226
--market-share 0.30
--current-hospitalized 1059
--date-first-hospitalized 2020-02-20
--mitigation-date 2020-03-21
--current-date 2020-04-08
--relative-contact-rate 0.54
--hospitalized-rate 0.025
--icu-rate 0.0075
--ventilated-rate 0.005
--infectious-days 10
--hospitalized-day 7
--icu-days 9
--ventilated-day 10
--n-days 120
--recovered 0

Data reading and prep

Read in the csv file and do a little data type fixing using the readr package.

adm_cen_long <- read_csv("data/mdrcid_adm_cen_long_df.csv",
    col_types = cols(id = col_integer(),
                     date = col_date(format = "%Y-%m-%d"),
                     mit_date = col_date(format = "%Y-%m-%d")))

# Make scenario a factor
adm_cen_long$scenario <- as.factor(adm_cen_long$scenario)

Here are the various measures that were captured.

unique(adm_cen_long$dispo_measure)
##  [1] "admits_hospitalized" "admits_icu"          "admits_ventilated"  
##  [4] "census_hospitalized" "census_icu"          "census_ventilated"  
##  [7] "avg_census"          "covid_census"        "covid_admits"       
## [10] "covid_discharges"    "covid_deaths"

Let’s create a smaller df to work with, just focusing on hospitalized.

hosp_measures <- c("admits_hospitalized", "census_hospitalized",
                   "covid_admits", "covid_census")
hosp_long <- adm_cen_long %>% 
  filter(dispo_measure %in% hosp_measures ) %>% 
  select(2:ncol(adm_cen_long))
rm(adm_cen_long)

Hospitalizations

Compute root mean squared error (RMSE) between projected and actual admits and census.

mdrcid_hosp_rmse <- hosp_long %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = dispo_measure, values_from = cases) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(covid_admits)) %>% 
  mutate(adm_err = admits_hospitalized - covid_admits,
         cen_err = census_hospitalized - covid_census) %>% 
  group_by(scenario, mit_date, rel_con_rate, inf_days) %>% 
  summarize(
    adm_rmse = sqrt(sum(adm_err ** 2)),
    cen_rmse = sqrt(sum(cen_err ** 2))
  ) %>% 
  arrange(adm_rmse)

Build some plot labels.

label <- sprintf("RMSE = %.1f\n", mdrcid_hosp_rmse$adm_rmse)
label <- str_c(label, sprintf("Mit Date = %s\n", format(mdrcid_hosp_rmse$mit_date, "%m-%d")))
label <- str_c(label, sprintf("Contact = %.2f\n", mdrcid_hosp_rmse$rel_con_rate))
label <- str_c(label, sprintf("Inf Days = %.1f\n", mdrcid_hosp_rmse$inf_days))
mdrcid_hosp_rmse$label <- label

Top 20 Fits for admits

Here are the 20 scenarios having the lowest RMSE values. It is interesting to see how mitigation dates affect fit. Compare these to the poor fits shown further down in the document. Also, relatively high values of relative contact rate are associated with better fits.

scenario_levels <-mdrcid_hosp_rmse[1:20, ]
scenario_levels$rmse_rank <- 1:20

adm_plot_df <- hosp_long %>% 
  filter(scenario %in% scenario_levels$scenario) %>% 
  filter(date < as.Date("2020-05-01")) %>% 
  filter(dispo_measure %in% c('admits_hospitalized', 'covid_admits')) %>% 
  left_join(scenario_levels, by=c("scenario"))

# Reorder the scenario factor by rmse
adm_plot_df$scenario <- as.character(adm_plot_df$scenario)
adm_plot_df$scenario <- as.factor(adm_plot_df$scenario)
adm_plot_df$scenario <- fct_reorder(adm_plot_df$scenario, adm_plot_df$rmse_rank, min)
  
ggplot(adm_plot_df) +
geom_line(aes(x=date, y=cases, colour=dispo_measure)) +
facet_wrap(~scenario, nrow=4 ) +
geom_text(
    data = scenario_levels,
    mapping = aes(x = as.Date("2020-03-01"), y = 300, label=label),
    hjust = "left"
  ) +
ggtitle("Top 20 Fits for admits")
## Warning: Removed 23 rows containing missing values (geom_path).
